The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), on Thursday, scheduled its outstanding North-West Zonal Congress for the purpose of electing a new Working Committee and National Ex-Officios for Saturday, February 12, 2022. Hon. Umaru M. Bature, National Organizing Secretary of the party, stated this in a statement on Thursday. “This is part of the resolution of the PDP National Working Committee (NWC) at its meeting on Wednesday, January 12, 2022,” the statement noted. According to him, the North-West Zonal Congress is slated to hold at the Zonal Headquarters of the party in Kaduna State. He said all critical stakeholders and teeming members of the party in the North-West Zone are “by this, informed and guided accordingly.”